gue. She wasn''t envied for the shallowness of appearance or the superficiality of status or possessions; she was envied for being uncommon and for possessing indomitable strength, something only a lifetime of suffering could shape.', 3711, 0), (155461, 'Anyone who crawls up from the gutter and makes something of themselves, despite the odds and despite others who tried to keep them down, must always be very proud of their achievements. They must never forget the struggles they went through, because they are a living example to those who wander in darkness, a staunch reminder that light is within reach if they can find the strength and determination to keep going.', 7486, 0), (155462, 'Miss Benson had the power; which some people have, of carrying her wishes through to fulfillment; her will was strong, her sense was excellent, and people yielded to her – they did not know why.', 640, 0), (155463, 'The strength to go on must come from within, not without, or it crushes instead of building up the heart.', 29257, 0), (155464, 'As one widow put it to me, “Strength doesn’t mean being able to stand up to anything, but being able to crawl on your belly a long, long time before you can stand up again.', 11069, 0), (155465, 'Would he ever have the strength to stop looking?', 28, 0), (155466, 'Life has pounded me downand thrashed me around,Time and time again,But I always get right back up,Because I still love life -Just as the earth still lovesThe rain.', 2678, 0), (155467, 'Her hand had a lot of strength gained through the process of gentleness.', 1262, 0), (155468, 'Taking someone for granted is same as checking the strength of a boat by making holes in it.', 15831, 0), (155469, 'Strength is wearing a smile even when you are wailing inside!', 29258, 0), (155470, 'You do not become outstanding by working on your weaknesses You become outstanding by focusing on your strenghts.', 11314, 0), (155471, 'Strength to your arm, then.', 169, 0), (155472, 'Was that his name? I never 